    "author_association": "COLLABORATOR",
    "body": "Yeah, that's my thought tbh, the file system provider is the only one I've ever seen a filter on, so I was curious if something else had tried to put filters on Test-Path.\r\n\r\nIt's an unusual use case too; Test-Path is usually used for testing complete paths, whereas -Filter is generally used to qualify searches (Get-ChildItem/Get-Item) and to filter out certain results. I kind of get the intent here, but I'm not really sure what providing -Filter would add here; you already have the path itself, so you can test if the string ends with a specific extension with more direct methods, or use Split-Path to retrieve just the filename if you have more complex patterns to test against. ðŸ˜• ",
